1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,333
<i> Hi, Jasmine.</i>

2
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:12,367
<i> What's the matter?</i>

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,667
<i> She's not breathing!</i>

4
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:16,400
<i>We suspect that she has
bronchopulmonary dysplasia.</i>

5
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>She can easily catch
colds, cough,</i>

6
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,200
<i> and sometimes even pneumonia.</i>

7
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,533
<i>Dad said he wanted to finance
my business.</i>

8
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:23,633
<i> Really?</i>

9
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,433
<i>You're materialistic
just like the others.</i>

10
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:29,800
<i>That's true, I want to secure
my child's future.</i>

11
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:31,900
<i>Now that you get along
with your dad,</i>

12
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> you can move into our mansion.</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> My favorite daughter-in-law.</i>

14
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,967
<i>Paolo, I heard Thea gave birth.</i>

15
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:41,400
<i>She's at the same hospital
where Jasmine is admitted.</i>

16
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,633
<i> She looks just like Jasmine.</i>

17
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,367
<i> They're siblings.</i>

18
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:49,233
What did you say?

19
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,567
What I meant was...

20
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:56,033
that Edward is Paolo's brother.

21
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:57,267
So it's not surprising that...

22
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,933
their children resemble
each other.

23
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,733
Why? What's the matter, Marj?

24
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:07,933
What are you guys thinking?

25
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:09,267
Nothing, Hon.

26
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,967
You're right,

27
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,933
Paolo and I are brothers.

28
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:20,000
I thought you said your child
is Jasmine's sibling.

29
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,267
What?

30
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,067
How is that possible?

31
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,767
Wait, but...

32
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:31,000
actually, why not?

33
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:33,200
They're cousins, right?

34
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:36,300
And they will grow up together.

35
00:01:36,433 --> 00:01:40,667
So, they can be like siblings.

36
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:42,833
You have a point.

37
00:01:42,967 --> 00:01:45,433
Wait, what did you name
this cute little baby?

38
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:46,867
What's her name?

39
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,800
Ashley, her name is Ashley.

40
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:51,533
It's from mom's second name.

41
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,300
I like it,

42
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:57,467
her name suits her.

43
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:02,267
Hi, Baby Ashley.

44
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,800
I'm giving you back to your mom.

45
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:11,900
Hi.

46
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:18,567
I love you, Baby Ashley.

47
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:21,533
Oh, grandmother will take
good care of you.

48
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:26,033
You don't look like your mom.

49
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:30,233
But I'm sure that you got your
features from the Torrecampos.

50
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:31,900
Why did you say that, Mom?

51
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:33,933
I was just thinking.

52
00:03:34,067 --> 00:03:36,533
Do you look like her
when you were a baby?

53
00:03:37,567 --> 00:03:38,700
It seems like...

54
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:41,200
She looks more like
your brother.

55
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,167
Baby Ashley looks like me.

56
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:52,667
<i> She got her features from me.</i>

57
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,467
Dad,

58
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:57,300
I'm surprised that
you dropped by here.

59
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:00,367
I didn't think that you'd want
to see my child.

60
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:03,733
Why would you think that?

61
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:05,600
Nothing, I just thought
you'd think...

62
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:09,300
she'll be just a loser like me.

63
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:11,133
I'm not exactly your favorite,
Dad.

64
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:15,033
Baby Ashley won't be a loser
like you.

65
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,467
She'll grow up to be tough...

66
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,467
and smart.

67
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,333
And she will excel
in everything.

68
00:04:25,367 --> 00:04:27,167
Right, Baby Ashley?

69
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,000
Excuse me,

70
00:04:37,133 --> 00:04:38,533
I have to take this call.

71
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:48,833
So pretty.

72
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:53,600
Love.

73
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,400
Love, I'm just going to check
on Jasmine.

74
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:02,467
Love, relax.

75
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,900
She's just sleeping.

76
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:08,567
I'm sorry I fell asleep
with her.

77
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:12,100
I lost a couple of nights
of sleep.

78
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:14,767
Are you sure you don't want
to get a private nurse for her?

79
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,733
No, Love, I can't rest easily.

80
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:21,533
I want to take care
of her myself.

81
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:23,133
I can handle it.

82
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:25,800
I promise,
until she gets better.

83
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:26,933
Okay,

84
00:06:27,067 --> 00:06:29,200
don't worry, I'll talk to dad.

85
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,733
I'm going to ask for a break
from work.

86
00:06:30,867 --> 00:06:33,867
So I can help you take care
of Jasmine.

87
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:40,333
Love, I don't want to distract
you from work.

88
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:44,733
Love, you're my priority.

89
00:06:44,867 --> 00:06:46,233
You and Jasmine.

90
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:47,733
Work can wait.

91
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,400
Okay? And you...

92
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:52,200
need some time for yourself.

93
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,500
For us.

94
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,800
Are you sure?

95
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,267
Of course.

96
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:04,100
You need me here.

97
00:07:05,267 --> 00:07:07,133
My daughter needs me, too.

98
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,133
Thank you.

99
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:14,333
Thank you for always being there
for me.

100
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:17,900
Thank you, Love.

101
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:19,933
I love you so much.

102
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,633
You're the best husband
in the world.

103
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:35,833
I'm so lucky to have you.

104
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:45,467
I'm just going to change
my clothes, so...

105
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,267
I can help you take care
of Jasmine.

106
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,733
I'll take care of her
for the rest of the night, okay?

107
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,000
Go on, get some rest.

108
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,833
I love you.

109
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:08,367
I love you more.

110
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,400
How's your daughter?

111
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,733
Jasmine is doing fine.

112
00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:33,500
I'm going to take care
of her tonight so that ...

113
00:08:33,633 --> 00:08:35,200
Marj can get some rest.

114
00:08:36,567 --> 00:08:40,700
At least you know which daughter
I'm talking about.

115
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:43,700
Because she's your only
daughter.

116
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,600
By the way,

117
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:52,600
Thea and Ashley are about to be
discharged from the hospital.

118
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,133
How is she?

119
00:08:57,667 --> 00:08:58,667
How is Ashley?

120
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:04,900
Your niece is pretty
and healthy, Paolo.

121
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:09,467
And don't ever forget that.

122
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:12,433
Ashley is your niece.

123
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:14,000
She is Edward's daughter.

124
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:19,900
Okay, Dad, I get it.

125
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:21,233
If I were you,

126
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:24,133
I wouldn't bother seeing...

127
00:09:24,267 --> 00:09:26,100
or getting to know her.

128
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,967
Because...

129
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:33,800
attachment creates
complications.

130
00:09:33,933 --> 00:09:35,967
And complications...

131
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,700
create crises.

132
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:42,700
And we didn't want more crises
around this household.

133
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:46,400
In this family.

134
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,267
Understood?

135
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:06,167
Hush, don't cry, it's daddy.

136
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:09,433
Okay, come on, Baby.

137
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:13,533
Don't cry, okay, it's daddy.

138
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:14,967
Hush, don't cry.

139
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,167
She doesn't seem to like me.

140
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:24,033
She's just not used to you yet.

141
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:25,533
She might be getting tired.

142
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,667
Give her to me.

143
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,700
Hush, Baby, don't cry.

144
00:10:41,367 --> 00:10:42,833
Look,

145
00:10:42,967 --> 00:10:45,233
she stopped crying
when you took her.

146
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:47,000
Hon, it's normal.

147
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:49,267
I carried her in my womb
for nine months.

148
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,767
She's used to me.

149
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:54,600
Are you hungry again?

150
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:00,167
Hello.

151
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:14,133
Is something troubling you?

152
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:18,833
It's nothing, just work stuff.

153
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:21,800
I need to make a phone call
real quick.

154
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:36,467
Are you getting bored here,
Ashley?

155
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,467
I know, right?

156
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,300
You want some fresh air.

157
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,267
Bigger space.

158
00:11:44,367 --> 00:11:45,633
Don't worry,

159
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,900
once we get discharged
from this hospital,

160
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:50,067
I'll take you out.

161
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,133
Somewhere fresh,

162
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:55,567
somewhere spacious.

163
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,233
A place a princess
like you deserves.

164
00:12:11,233 --> 00:12:13,100
<i> Hi, Mom.</i>

165
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:17,400
I don't know what to do anymore
to make myself stronger.

166
00:12:17,567 --> 00:12:20,033
With every breath she takes,
I feel anxious.

167
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:21,467
With every sound
from the monitor,

168
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,867
it feels like my heart
is about to explode.

169
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,533
I feel so bad for my baby.

170
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:28,833
I wish we could trade places.

171
00:12:28,967 --> 00:12:32,033
I know I can handle being sick,
but my baby...

172
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,600
I don't know what to do.

173
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:40,533
Marj, don't talk like that.

174
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:43,233
You wouldn't want to get sick.

175
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:46,967
You need to be strong.

176
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,567
Because you are her lifeline.

177
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:51,400
If you want to take care
of her,

178
00:12:51,533 --> 00:12:54,300
you need to care for yourself
too, sweetie.

179
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,167
Marj,

180
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:05,100
take care of yourself, okay?

181
00:13:05,233 --> 00:13:10,367
Because I'm not with you
anymore.

182
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:15,933
Don't neglect yourself,
because...

183
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:20,933
I'm a big boy now,
I have to go to a big school.

184
00:13:23,367 --> 00:13:27,367
And don't you neglect yourself.

185
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:31,633
You need to get stronger
for baby Jasmine.

186
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:33,600
Marj,

187
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:36,867
listen to your brother,
he's right.

188
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:39,600
Marj,

189
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:44,167
you need to be strong.

190
00:13:45,233 --> 00:13:48,167
Your husband supports you,
doesn't he?

191
00:13:49,233 --> 00:13:51,167
We're in a difficult situation
right now, Mom,

192
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:54,100
but Paolo and I are managing.

193
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:56,300
Jobert is right.

194
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:58,833
Don't worry, okay?

195
00:13:58,967 --> 00:14:01,567
I will take care of myself.

196
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:02,900
Okay.

197
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:05,700
I love you.

198
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:09,167
I love you too, Marj.

199
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,867
Hey, sweetie,

200
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,200
what's with the long face?

201
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:39,967
You should be celebrating.

202
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:43,700
Didn't you just launch
your own company online?

203
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:49,200
One of the investors pulled out.

204
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:50,800
I lost a big investment.

205
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,800
My business is seriously
undercapitalized right now,

206
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,800
and if I can't figure
something out,

207
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:57,600
we're going to end up
in a cash flow crisis, Mom.

208
00:14:57,733 --> 00:15:00,667
Oh my God, that sounds
like a big problem.

209
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:03,800
But you know what to do.

210
00:15:03,933 --> 00:15:06,000
Why don't you ask your dad
for help?

211
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,867
No, no, no, Mom!

212
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,300
I can't ask him for help, and...

213
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:13,033
he doesn't need to know
about this.

214
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:15,800
Anyway, I have a lot of meetings
with...

215
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:19,067
potential investors lined up,
including a Cebu-based client.

216
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,233
I think...

217
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:22,000
it's promising.

218
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,533
Cebu?

219
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:25,033
Yes, Cebu.

220
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:29,900
Over there, the operation
expenses will be lower.

221
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:32,633
I can stabilize the cash flow.

222
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:35,400
And most importantly,
I'll be away from dad.

223
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,367
I can do everything I want
freely.

224
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,967
And honestly,

225
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,500
that is important to me,
I need it.

226
00:15:43,633 --> 00:15:45,400
Wait a minute.

227
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:46,733
Are you saying you're leaving?

228
00:15:46,867 --> 00:15:48,800
You'll relocate to Cebu?

229
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:50,467
You're leaving us?

230
00:15:54,233 --> 00:15:55,567
I have no choice, Mom.

231
00:15:57,567 --> 00:16:01,133
The investor who's going to help
me with my problem is there.

232
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:03,700
And I can't fail, Mom, I can't.

233
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,000
Not this time.

234
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:08,900
Sweetie,

235
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:13,033
that decision is not just yours
anymore.

236
00:16:13,167 --> 00:16:16,300
Your choices will affect
your family.

237
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:18,233
Have you told Thea about this?

238
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:29,433
Hi, Ma'am Thea.

239
00:16:29,567 --> 00:16:31,267
You got discharged
from the hospital?

240
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,567
Yes, we got discharged
yesterday.

241
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:37,333
I brought Ashley here because
I want to surprise mom.

242
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:39,867
I'm sure she'll be happy
to see her granddaughter.

243
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,567
Oh my, but Ma'am Regina
is not home.

244
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:45,967
She left early this morning.

245
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,900
Is that so?

246
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:49,067
That's such a shame.

247
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,967
I was really hoping they'd get
to see each other today.

248
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,133
What about Marj?

249
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:54,900
Ma'am Marj is upstairs.

250
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:57,733
Her brother and her mom came
to visit her.

251
00:16:57,867 --> 00:17:00,467
Sir Paolo's in the other
living room.

252
00:17:08,167 --> 00:17:10,000
I know that you'll get better
soon.

253
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:13,300
Because you take after your mom.

254
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:14,467
A fighter.

255
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,400
Sir,

256
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:23,033
excuse me, it's time
for the baby's medication.

257
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:25,833
I'll bring her upstairs
to Ma'am Marj.

258
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,467
Why?

259
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Nothing, Ma'am.

260
00:17:36,133 --> 00:17:41,167
I'm just looking at how cute
Baby Ashley is.

261
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:42,433
Of course,

262
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:44,700
my daughter is pretty.

263
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,667
She is a Torrecampo.

264
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,867
She looks just like her daddy,
doesn't she?

265
00:17:50,433 --> 00:17:51,767
Excuse me,

266
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:53,967
I'm going to say hi to Paolo.

267
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:57,067
I'm sure he'll be happy to see
our baby.

268
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:01,433
Edward's baby!

269
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,933
Bye.

270
00:18:07,867 --> 00:18:10,167
<i>- I'll follow you upstairs.
- Okay, Sir.</i>

271
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:14,600
Look how cute that little
baby is.

272
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:19,833
- So cute!
- Hi, Uncle Paolo.

273
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:27,533
Baby Ashley just wants to say hi
to her Uncle Paolo.

274
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:36,933
I'm bringing baby Jasmine
upstairs.

275
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:38,467
Baby.

276
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:39,667
Excuse me.

277
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:48,900
You never visited us
at the hospital.

278
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,233
What are you doing here?

279
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:57,733
Go ahead,

280
00:18:58,767 --> 00:19:00,900
hold your daughter.

281
00:19:11,133 --> 00:19:12,667
My gosh, Paolo.

282
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,433
Wouldn't you even look at her?

283
00:19:16,467 --> 00:19:18,567
I didn't create her
all by myself.

284
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,367
Please, Thea,
don't do this here.

285
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,633
So when are you going
to hold her?

286
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:26,633
No one can see us.

287
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:28,600
Nobody's around anyway.

288
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,767
Come on, Paolo,

289
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:35,767
give her a chance to see you.

290
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:37,433
To hold you.

291
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,533
You know what?
This is a bad idea.

292
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:44,533
Do you really have no intention
of even seeing her?

293
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:46,600
Or at least holding her?

294
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:51,433
I'm not asking you to take
responsibility for her.

295
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,567
We are way past that now.

296
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:01,900
Baby Ashley is such
a lively child.

297
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,333
Oh my, she's so hyper.

298
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:05,633
But that's actually
a good thing.

299
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,433
At least she's not
like the other child.

300
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:10,233
Always sick and irritable.

301
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:14,833
I feel like a little wind
could sweep her away.

302
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:16,567
So I really wouldn't
be surprised...

303
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:19,700
if Sir Greg ends up liking
Baby Ashley more.

304
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:22,833
<i>Am I right? Sir Greg doesn't
like the weak ones.</i>

305
00:20:22,967 --> 00:20:24,167
<i> Is that right, Yolly?</i>

306
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,800
Yolly?

307
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:29,500
Why are you so serious?

308
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:30,833
It's nothing,

309
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,367
it's just that I've been taking
care of the Torrecampo kids...

310
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,833
for a long time.

311
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:36,767
Since Edward and Paolo
are still young.

312
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:37,867
But...

313
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:38,967
It's just...

314
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:41,300
I don't know.

315
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,000
What is it, Yolly?

316
00:21:14,467 --> 00:21:15,400
Yolly?

317
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:19,533
The baby.

318
00:21:19,667 --> 00:21:20,833
Why?

319
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:25,533
She looks like Sir Paolo
when he was a baby.

320
00:21:29,667 --> 00:21:31,800
She doesn't behave like that
with Edward.

321
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,767
Don't be like that.

322
00:21:37,567 --> 00:21:39,200
What's so wrong with...

323
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,133
this stolen moment, right?

324
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,867
Paolo, you're her father.

325
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:48,067
No matter how much you try
to avoid her,

326
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:51,167
your body recognizes her
as yours.

327
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:53,933
And she recognizes you
as her father.

328
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:55,333
No one else.

329
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,433
Come on, Yolly, of course,

330
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:08,500
they resemble each other,
she is his niece.

331
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:13,967
And that was a long time ago,
don't tell me...

332
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,900
you can still clearly remember
them as babies.

333
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:18,767
Yolly.

334
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:21,900
You could have been confused.

335
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:23,133
You're probably right.

336
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:32,900
Love?

337
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:39,067
Are you okay?

338
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,800
Why do you look like
you're about to cry....

339
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:42,933
while holding Baby Ashley?

340
00:22:58,233 --> 00:23:00,600
Oh no, it's just
my first time...

341
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:02,633
seeing her.

342
00:23:02,933 --> 00:23:04,433
I was thinking of Jasmine,

343
00:23:04,567 --> 00:23:06,067
now she will have a playmate.

344
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,400
I just...

345
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:13,700
can't imagine.

346
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:17,567
Your husband is just
feeling guilty.

347
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:25,033
Because he and Edward
are still not getting along.

348
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,633
That's why he didn't get
to visit us at the hospital.

349
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:33,633
Okay, we're going to go now.

350
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:36,633
We just stopped by.

351
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:39,200
I want Mom Regina to see her.

352
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:41,200
But she's not here.

353
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:43,333
But at least,

354
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:46,800
she gets to meet her Uncle
Paolo.

355
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:48,233
Finally.

356
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:53,500
- Okay.
- Okay, take care.

357
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,900
- Bye, Baby.
- Bye.

358
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:05,967
- Love...
- Yeah?

359
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,600
Are you sure you're okay?

360
00:24:11,133 --> 00:24:12,667
Yes.

361
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,967
I'm just feeling vulnerable.

362
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,033
Or maybe I'm just tired.

363
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:19,267
Because we've been busy
with Jasmine, right?

364
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:24,867
By the way,
dad just sent me a message.

365
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:28,167
He's inviting us to dinner
this Friday.

366
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,233
He says it's a family
business meeting.

367
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,567
It will be held here at home.

368
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:34,400
Is your dad aware that you're
going to take a little break...

369
00:24:34,533 --> 00:24:35,467
from the business?

370
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,333
To take care of Jasmine?

371
00:24:37,467 --> 00:24:39,933
The HR probably informed
him already.

372
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:42,667
And I'm still working
at home anyway.

373
00:24:45,667 --> 00:24:49,400
So you haven't talked to him
in person yet.

374
00:24:51,133 --> 00:24:55,167
I planned to tell him
over dinner.

375
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:13,367
Once we activate
the next phase,

376
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:16,233
revenue could double
within the year, Edward.

377
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:18,567
Finally,

378
00:25:18,833 --> 00:25:22,700
we can build our own
Torrecampo Empire, Hon.

379
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:24,567
Definitely,

380
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:26,433
with Edward's team
and my structure,

381
00:25:26,567 --> 00:25:29,667
we can build something big
in Cebu.

382
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:33,200
Wait, sorry.

383
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:34,333
Where?

384
00:25:36,133 --> 00:25:38,433
You mean where in Cebu?

385
00:25:38,567 --> 00:25:39,967
We're targeting Lahug.

386
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:42,000
That's where the main
operations will be.

387
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,033
By the way, Edward,

388
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:46,700
when do you plan to relocate?

389
00:25:46,833 --> 00:25:48,700
I'm assuming soon, since...

390
00:25:48,833 --> 00:25:50,300
timing is everything.

391
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,733
Relocate?

392
00:25:53,867 --> 00:25:55,300
Yes,

393
00:25:55,433 --> 00:25:58,533
so I can take care of onboarding
and permits over there.

394
00:25:58,667 --> 00:26:02,600
Everything will go smoothly
with a clear schedule.

395
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,433
How come I am only
hearing about this now?

396
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:13,967
You made a decision
without me?

397
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:25,933
I'm stepping down as CEO
of Torrecampo Realty.

398
00:26:26,067 --> 00:26:27,900
I can prove to him
that I'm not a failure.

399
00:26:28,033 --> 00:26:29,900
Just make sure of it,
Edward, okay?

400
00:26:30,033 --> 00:26:30,900
You can't fail.

401
00:26:31,033 --> 00:26:33,100
You've been preparing
for this for years.

402
00:26:33,233 --> 00:26:37,200
Greg had other women before.

403
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:39,567
Now we're on the same boat,
Marjorie.

404
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,333
Jasmine and I need you, too.

405
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:42,800
So don't you ever forget that.

406
00:26:42,967 --> 00:26:45,300
We will take everything
that is ours.

407
00:26:45,433 --> 00:26:48,700
Because you will be
the rightful heir...

408
00:26:48,833 --> 00:26:52,667
of everything
the Torrecampos have.

409
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:54,233
Ready when you are.

410
00:26:56,433 --> 00:26:57,767
We got this.

411
00:26:57,900 --> 00:26:59,967
It's our anniversary.

412
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:01,800
You thought I forgot,
didn't you?

413
00:27:01,933 --> 00:27:03,233
Love, you haven't opened
your present yet.

414
00:27:03,367 --> 00:27:05,267
Love, this is an important
matter, I'll be right back.

415
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,233
I can't drop everything for...

416
00:27:07,367 --> 00:27:08,700
For us?

417
00:27:08,833 --> 00:27:11,200
Happy 16th Anniversary.

418
00:27:12,633 --> 00:27:16,033
You need to accept that
you're not the only one...

419
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,100
in your husband's life anymore
